                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>30 feet. A feeling of recklessness surrounds a gambling devil. When a non-fiend creature enters the aura or begins its turn in the aura, it must attempt a @Check[will|dc:31] save.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected and is temporarily immune to Risk Aura for 24 hours.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The next time the creature rolls a d20, it must roll twice. If either roll is a natural 20, the creature uses that result; otherwise, it must take the lower of the two results.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but applies to all of the creature's d20 rolls as long as it remains in the aura.</p>"
